               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <subc>I,2</subc> [denominatum a <foreign xml:lang="he">מֶלַח</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܡܶܠܚܳܐ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="ar">مِلْحٌ</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> sal </t:quote></cit>, ut <foreign xml:lang="he">מָלַח</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܡܠܰܚ</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="ar">مَلَحَ</foreign>] <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> sallere </t:quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> sale condire </t:quote></cit> <ref cRef="Marc." loc="9,49">Marc. 9,49</ref>. </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mallǝḥa</t:quote></cit> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልሐ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mallǝḥa</t:quote></cit> <subc>I,2</subc> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይሜልሕ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይመልሕ፡</foreign> «<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">assaisonner</t:quote></cit>» ― <foreign xml:lang="am">አጣፈጠ፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BNFabb217">BNFabb217</ref>, fol.33r. <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 74</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልሐ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mallǝḥa</t:quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">season with salt</t:quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">make tasty</t:quote></cit> (denominative of <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">malḥ</t:quote></cit>); note that G. <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልሐ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">malḥa</t:quote></cit> or <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mallǝḥa</t:quote></cit> is also rendered by <bibl><ptr target="bm:AlaqaTayya1965MSawasew"/><citedRange unit="page"> 37</citedRange></bibl> and <bibl><ptr target="bm:TasfaS1945GeezWords"/><citedRange unit="page"> 9</citedRange></bibl> ‘do, work’ (also KG <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mǝlḥ</t:quote></cit> ‘work’), possibly ‘do good work’, salt being the symbol of good deeds. It could also be that <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልሐ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">malḥa</t:quote></cit> is for <lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልኀ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">malḫa</t:quote></cit> below, and the general meaning ‘do, work’ refers to all the activities expressed by <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">malḫa</t:quote></cit>. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/><citedRange unit="page"> 343</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> </sense></entry>
